and he agreed to record

11:10.030 --> 11:12.169
Mr. Bishop's attorney,
Cary Agos.

11:12.200 --> 11:14.395
GENEVA:
And do you have that
recording for this court?

11:14.440 --> 11:15.998
Objection, Your
Honor. Hearsay.
I think we've been

11:16.040 --> 11:18.008
over this, Your Honor.
Forfeiture by wrongdoing.

11:18.040 --> 11:19.701
Yep, as I
warned you,

11:19.740 --> 11:22.038
Ms. Lockhart,
this recording is subject

11:22.080 --> 11:24.071
to a hearsay
exception.

11:24.110 --> 11:25.941
So, ladies and
gentlemen of the jury,

11:25.980 --> 11:28.949
I want you to know...
Excuse me, gentlemen.

11:28.980 --> 11:31.949
There is no cross talk
in the jury box.

11:31.990 --> 11:35.118
The only one in court who should
be talking is me. Now,

11:35.160 --> 11:37.981
I will allow this tape
to be played,

11:38.030 --> 11:40.225
but I want you to take
into account that the defense

11:40.260 --> 11:42.421
will not be able
to cross-examine

11:42.460 --> 11:44.963
the person who
recorded the tape.

11:45.000 --> 11:46.422
