23:12.720 --> 23:14.119
DIANE:
Oh, Your Honor, I object.

23:14.160 --> 23:15.616
CUESTA:
And you're overruled.

23:15.660 --> 23:18.458
Sheriff, please
excuse the jurors.

23:18.490 --> 23:21.095
Uh, all except
juror number 11.

23:21.130 --> 23:24.019
Please escort
him to chambers.

23:24.070 --> 23:26.425
ALICIA:
Why?

23:26.470 --> 23:28.438
What happened?
CARY:
I don't know.

23:28.470 --> 23:30.768
They took our only
slam-dunk juror into chambers.

23:30.810 --> 23:32.437
You think
Geneva's trying to bounce her?

23:32.470 --> 23:34.438
Him, and it looks like it.

23:34.480 --> 23:35.799
Well, how's the alternate?

23:35.840 --> 23:37.603
Bad.

23:37.650 --> 23:38.799
Both are bad.

23:38.850 --> 23:40.477
Keep me in touch?

23:40.520 --> 23:43.080
Thank you for
coming, Alicia.

23:43.120 --> 23:44.485
I know you
must be busy.

23:44.520 --> 23:46.488
Oh, never too busy
for Grace's teachers.

23:46.520 --> 23:48.511
So, I-I know you
want this note back.

23:48.560 --> 23:50.653
I'm so sorry how this got
blown out of proportion.

23:50.690 --> 23:52.829
I knew you were joking,
but the liability issues...

23:52.860 --> 23:54.452
I understand.

23:54.500 --> 23:56.923
So, Grace said
you wanted to talk to me?

23:56.960 --> 23:59.622
My husband works with
the teacher's union,

23:59.670 --> 24:02.537
and over the last five years,
there has been a decrease

24:02.570 --> 24:05.505
in school crime oversight
in the S.A.'s office.

24:05.540 --> 24:07.633
Really?
Yes.

24:07.680 --> 24:09.500
It's terrible.

24:09.540 --> 24:12.475
There used to be a task force
made up of eight teachers

24:12.510 --> 24:15.217
who would advise the state's
attorney on school crime.

24:15.250 --> 24:18.219
And you would like
to have that back?

24:18.250 --> 24:20.559
Yes, we would love
to have that back.

24:20.590 --> 24:23.582
With eight positions set aside
for teacher union members.

24:23.630 --> 24:26.451
That would be
really great for us.

24:28.230 --> 24:29.595
Just give it to her.
No.

24:29.630 --> 24:30.699
It's patronage.
Well, of course,

24:30.730 --> 24:31.890
it's patronage, Alicia.

24:31.930 --> 24:32.999
How do you think
this thing works?

24:33.030 --> 24:34.531
Eli, I said "no" to patronage.

24:34.570 --> 24:36.037
And I congratulate you
on that stance, Alicia,

24:36.070 --> 24:37.935
but you need this note
not to circulate.

24:37.970 --> 24:39.562
Alicia, it's important

24:39.610 --> 24:40.770
to show that you stand up
to patronage,

24:40.810 --> 24:42.607
but the key word here is "show."

24:42.640 --> 24:44.244
There is some patronage
that everybody accepts.

24:44.280 --> 24:45.907
Your husband
accepted...
Oy.

24:45.950 --> 24:48.771
Exactly. I'm not going
to be like Peter.

24:52.090 --> 24:54.650
You know. Ethics.

24:56.620 --> 24:58.622
Mr. Fratti, is it?

24:58.660 --> 24:59.957
It is. What's wrong?

24:59.990 --> 25:02.493
Have a seat.

25:04.170 --> 25:09.198
Uh, I have a note here
from an anonymous juror reading,

25:09.240 --> 25:12.300
"I thinkjuror number 11
might be partially deaf.

25:12.340 --> 25:15.673
"He is having trouble
understanding the proceedings,

25:15.710 --> 25:19.646
and he continually asks those
around him what's going on."

25:19.680 --> 25:21.318
Now, are you partially deaf,
Mr. Fratti?

25:21.350 --> 25:23.545
No.
GENEVA:
Your Honor, I...

25:23.590 --> 25:25.546
Excuse me.
You told us not to talk.

25:25.590 --> 25:27.558
Stop it. 1-1 understand
what's going on here.

25:27.590 --> 25:30.184
Ms. Lockhart, you think
he's pro-defense,

25:30.220 --> 25:33.189
and you want him to stay, and,
Ms. Pine, you want him to go.

25:33.230 --> 25:35.619
Well, shush, both of you.

25:35.660 --> 25:38.163
Now, Mr. Fratti,

25:38.200 --> 25:40.065
is there anything
that would prevent you

25:40.100 --> 25:41.863
from understanding this trial?

25:41.900 --> 25:43.868
I didn't hide anything.
I know that, sir.

25:43.910 --> 25:45.332
Is there anything

25:45.370 --> 25:47.258
that would prevent
your understanding?

25:49.840 --> 25:52.809
During certain moments
of stress,

25:52.850 --> 25:55.148
I can suffer from APD--

25:55.180 --> 25:56.909
Auditory Processing Disorder.

25:56.950 --> 25:59.043
CUESTA:
And why didn't you mention this
during voir dire?

25:59.090 --> 26:01.888
Because it only
rarely affects me,

26:01.920 --> 26:03.649
which was the question
put to me.

26:03.690 --> 26:05.749
On occasion,
I can have difficulty

26:05.790 --> 26:08.258
with the sequencing of words,
or confuse similar sounds.

26:08.300 --> 26:10.325
But did this

26:10.360 --> 26:12.225
affect you during trial?

26:14.200 --> 26:16.088
and I have certain
coping mechanisms...

26:16.140 --> 26:18.700
Your Honor, this is...
He says he has
followed the trial.

26:18.740 --> 26:20.674
Wait, wait, wait.

26:20.710 --> 26:23.338
Mr. Fratti,
I have a question for you.

26:24.710 --> 26:27.076
What waxing the number

26:27.110 --> 26:28.941
of the last wideness?

26:28.980 --> 26:30.379
Your Honor,
it is not a common name.

26:30.420 --> 26:32.240
GENEVA:
How is that relevant?

26:32.290 --> 26:34.656
Ms. Lockhart, please!
We're not in a schoolyard.

26:34.690 --> 26:37.921
Now, what did I ask you,
Mr. Fratti?

26:37.960 --> 26:39.655
You asked me the name
of the last witness,

26:39.690 --> 26:41.624
and I think
it was Kalinda something?

26:41.660 --> 26:43.252
GENEVA:
Your Honor, may I
ask a question?

26:43.300 --> 26:46.189
No, but I will.
The question, Mr. Fratti,

26:46.230 --> 26:50.189
is whether Cary Agos hurt lemons

26:50.240 --> 26:53.903
bussing the important
tree-mills of honeycuts.

27:08.920 --> 27:11.252
Um, I'm sorry.

27:11.290 --> 27:13.929
Ithought
you were innocent.

27:16.960 --> 27:19.292
I need your help, Kalinda.
We don't have

27:19.330 --> 27:21.764
a strong
enough case.

27:37.990 --> 27:40.879
Um, I'm sorry.

27:40.920 --> 27:42.808
Ithought
you were innocent.

27:45.890 --> 27:47.755
I need your help, Kalinda.

27:47.800 --> 27:49.950
We don't have
a strong enough case.

27:50.000 --> 27:52.889
Let me see
what I can do, okay?

27:55.300 --> 27:56.858
ALICIA:
How's it going?

27:56.900 --> 27:58.458
Notgood.
Cary lost his juror.

27:58.510 --> 28:00.831
Damn it.
How can I help?

28:00.880 --> 28:02.279
We need to get a lead on Dante.

28:02.310 --> 28:03.777
Bishop's man?

28:03.810 --> 28:05.141
Yeah. He's the only one
still alive

28:05.180 --> 28:06.943
who heard what was edited
out of the wire.

28:06.980 --> 28:09.210
I can't get anything from Finn.

28:09.250 --> 28:11.889
Alicia, he knows
that Cary is innocent, he knows

28:11.920 --> 28:13.444
this is a wrongful prosecution,
and

28:13.490 --> 28:16.050
he will hear it if you say it.

28:16.090 --> 28:20.186
Just ask him for any lead that
could get us to Dante, anything.

28:20.230 --> 28:22.152
Okay, I'll see what I can do.
ELI:
You're kidding me.

28:22.200 --> 28:24.828
JOHNNY:
"I will personally come down
to your office, and knife you

28:24.870 --> 28:25.894
in your lower intestines..."

28:25.930 --> 28:27.420
ELI:
"You will most probably

28:27.470 --> 28:29.199
bleed out."

28:29.240 --> 28:30.867
You know, for some reason,
I thought this was

28:30.910 --> 28:32.866
gonna be funnier.
Where is it, on a blog?

28:32.910 --> 28:34.969
Yeah. The Correspondent blog.
Give her the patronage, Alicia.

28:35.010 --> 28:36.500
What's it matter now?
You need the union.

28:36.540 --> 28:38.178
(sighs)

28:38.210 --> 28:41.179
I have to go.

28:41.220 --> 28:43.176
MAN:
Order up.

28:43.220 --> 28:45.438
Cleanup. Can I get
cleanup over here?

28:45.490 --> 28:47.344
(laughing)

28:47.390 --> 28:50.052
Well, you succeeded

28:50.090 --> 28:52.285
in finding
the ugliest diner in Chicago.

28:52.330 --> 28:54.093
(sighs)
Oh!

28:54.130 --> 28:55.927
Well, it helps that we
both smell like wet dogs.

28:55.960 --> 28:57.894
(laughs)

28:57.930 --> 29:01.866
And pancakes. Perfect.

29:04.310 --> 29:07.131
So, fellow lavwer...
Mm-hmm.

29:07.170 --> 29:10.776
I have a request that's gonna
make us both uncomfortable.

29:10.810 --> 29:13.244
Great. That's why I'm here.
You heard about Cary's trial?

29:13.280 --> 29:15.316
He lost a juror.
Yes.

29:15.350 --> 29:17.272
We need to find Dante.

29:17.320 --> 29:19.311
He's the only one still alive

29:19.350 --> 29:21.557
who can testify
that Cary's innocent,

29:21.590 --> 29:23.979
that the wire was edited.
(thunder crackling)

29:24.030 --> 29:25.258
You know I can't
say anything.
I do.

29:25.290 --> 29:27.121
It's just, I thought...

29:27.160 --> 29:28.559
(indistinct chatter)

29:28.600 --> 29:31.990
Well, that's not good.

29:32.030 --> 29:34.089
WAITRESS:
It's the storm. Hold on.

29:34.140 --> 29:36.961
You were saying?

29:37.000 --> 29:38.467
(rain pouring)

29:38.510 --> 29:42.037
I was saying?
No, I think you-you were...

29:42.080 --> 29:44.298
Oh, yeah. Um...

29:44.350 --> 29:46.306
yeah.

29:46.350 --> 29:49.012
I can't say anything.

29:49.050 --> 29:51.348
(guitar plays
upbeat, gentle melody)

29:51.390 --> 29:53.858
(singing in Italian)

29:53.890 --> 29:56.358
(laughs)

29:56.390 --> 29:58.449
You're kidding.
(laughs)

29:58.490 --> 30:00.321
(laughing)

30:00.360 --> 30:02.021
Of course.

30:02.060 --> 30:04.858
So, you can't say anything?

30:04.900 --> 30:07.266
I can't.

30:12.210 --> 30:14.371
What's that?

30:14.410 --> 30:16.833
I can't say anything.

30:16.880 --> 30:20.179
Surveillance photos
from Bishop's house.

30:20.210 --> 30:22.917
Anybody entering
or exiting.

30:22.950 --> 30:25.885
Of course, I don't know
how you got 'em, because, uh,

30:25.920 --> 30:29.117
well... I can't say anything.

30:35.200 --> 30:36.553
BISHOP:
I wasn't even there!

30:36.600 --> 30:38.397
WOMAN:
Yes, you were!
Why are you lying to me?

30:38.430 --> 30:41.194
BISHOP:
I'm not lying.
You won't listen.

30:41.240 --> 30:43.435
(arguing continues indistinctly)

30:45.910 --> 30:48.003
My dad's fighting.

30:48.040 --> 30:49.439
Oh.
(indistinct shouting)

30:49.480 --> 30:52.074
He'll be right here.
It's just his girlfriend.

30:52.110 --> 30:53.509
Sure.

30:53.550 --> 30:55.074
BISHOP:
It's not...
it's not your business!

30:57.120 --> 30:59.179
Do you work
with my dad?

30:59.220 --> 31:01.415
Uh, sometimes.

31:01.460 --> 31:05.282
Do you come here
after school?

31:05.330 --> 31:07.150
Yeah. Why?

31:07.190 --> 31:09.397
No reason.
Is that at 3:00?

31:09.430 --> 31:12.092
BISHOP:
Okay? This is not gonna work

31:12.130 --> 31:14.439
if you don't trust me.
You need to trust me.

31:14.470 --> 31:17.064
Very adult.

31:18.540 --> 31:21.134
Dylan, it's time
to go to bed.

31:21.180 --> 31:22.329
I know.

31:25.150 --> 31:27.243
BISHOP:
I love you.
DYLAN: You, too.

31:28.520 --> 31:30.909
What do you need, Kalinda?

31:33.190 --> 31:35.317
Dante.

31:35.360 --> 31:38.022
Yeah. A lot of people
need Dante.

31:38.060 --> 31:39.425
Why are you coming to me?

31:39.460 --> 31:41.428
Because I think you
know where he is.

31:41.460 --> 31:44.167
And if you wanted him
to testify, he would.

31:44.200 --> 31:46.327
All right, then maybe
I don't want him to testify.

31:46.370 --> 31:48.167
(sighs)
It's-it's a little late.

31:48.200 --> 31:49.997
Can-can we do this
another time?

31:50.040 --> 31:52.201
I have some photos
I need you to see.

31:55.110 --> 31:58.147
These are state's attorney

31:58.180 --> 32:00.444
surveillance photos
of your house.

32:05.250 --> 32:08.959
Kalinda... I know you like Cary,

32:08.990 --> 32:13.381
but you shouldn't be here
saying that to me.

32:13.430 --> 32:16.319
And you shouldn't be here
with such a weak weapon.

32:16.360 --> 32:18.464
These are four
known drug dealers

32:18.500 --> 32:20.092
entering your front door.

32:20.130 --> 32:21.358
Yeah, well, too bad.

32:21.400 --> 32:23.391
I'm not there. Do you see me
in that picture?

32:23.440 --> 32:26.000
Oh, you don't need
to be there, sir.

32:26.040 --> 32:28.429
For them to arrest me,
I sure do.

32:28.480 --> 32:30.630
This is not about you.

32:30.680 --> 32:33.604
This is about Dylan.

32:37.350 --> 32:40.478
There's enough here for Child
Services to take your son away.

32:46.790 --> 32:49.497
These are copies.

32:49.530 --> 32:52.169
They are not originals.

32:55.800 --> 32:58.360
Anyone know you're here?

32:59.540 --> 33:01.701
Yeah.

33:03.540 --> 33:06.247
What the hell do you think
you're doing?!

33:06.280 --> 33:08.475
Who do you think I am?
I'm not...

33:08.520 --> 33:10.545
No. You come here
to threaten me?

33:10.580 --> 33:13.583
You come here
to threaten my son?
I'm not threatening you.

33:13.620 --> 33:16.111
Look, we want to help you...

33:16.160 --> 33:18.526
but... we need your help.

33:18.560 --> 33:20.721
Get out of here, Kalinda...

33:20.760 --> 33:23.593
before I think
about this too much.

33:25.730 --> 33:28.164
*

33:37.580 --> 33:39.673
How did you
find Dante?

33:39.710 --> 33:41.712
Don't tell me.

33:43.150 --> 33:45.118
You're a lifesaver.

33:45.150 --> 33:47.584
Looking forward
to this being over.

33:49.460 --> 33:51.451
DIANE:
Uh, Your Honor,
we have a new name

33:51.490 --> 33:55.324
to add to the witness list--
Dante Wallach.

34:02.200 --> 34:03.269
DANTE:
Dante Wallach.

34:03.300 --> 34:05.063
DIANE:
And you know the defendant?

34:05.110 --> 34:07.101
That guy? Yeah.
And you were
in Mr. Bishop's

34:07.140 --> 34:09.074
kitchen with him

34:09.110 --> 34:11.078
on May 25 of this year?

34:11.110 --> 34:12.270
Yeah.
And did you

34:12.310 --> 34:15.313
ask him questions
about your business?

34:17.850 --> 34:19.488
DANTE:
Yeah.

34:19.520 --> 34:23.149
DIANE: And you have heard
the prosecutor's tape

34:23.190 --> 34:24.122
of this conversation?

34:24.160 --> 34:25.422
DANTE:
The wire? Yeah.

34:25.460 --> 34:27.781
DIANE:
And does this tape...

34:27.830 --> 34:30.151
reflect your conversation?

34:30.200 --> 34:31.599
DANTE:
Yeah. I-I mean...

34:31.630 --> 34:33.791
What do you mean?
Did Cary tell you

34:33.830 --> 34:35.639
how to break the law?

34:36.670 --> 34:38.103
Yeah.

34:38.140 --> 34:40.131
DIANE:
Uh, Mr. Wallach,

34:40.170 --> 34:41.774
let me ask you again...

34:41.810 --> 34:44.779
GENEVA:
I think he already answered.
I am asking whether Cary

34:44.810 --> 34:47.142
told you that
he couldn't help you

34:47.180 --> 34:50.809
break the law.
DANTE: No, he told us
how to break the law.

34:50.850 --> 34:54.149
How to be smart about it.
DIANE:
Uh, Mr. Wallach, excuse me,

34:54.190 --> 34:57.216
but you told us outside
of this court the exact opposite

34:57.260 --> 34:59.228
of what you're saying here.
DANTE:
Nah.

34:59.260 --> 35:00.659
Maybe you misheard it.
Is someone

35:00.690 --> 35:02.248
threatening you, Mr. Wallach?

35:02.300 --> 35:04.393
Objection, Your Honor.
Argumentative.

35:04.430 --> 35:06.193
DIANE:
Uh, then I need a sidebar,
Your Honor.

35:06.230 --> 35:08.289
CUESTA:
Sure, come on up.
Let's do this.

35:08.340 --> 35:10.558
(quietly): Don't you
ever threaten me again,
do you understand?

35:10.600 --> 35:12.568
Get him to tell the truth.

35:12.610 --> 35:14.578
I need to know that
you understand, Kalinda.

35:14.610 --> 35:16.237
I understand, sir.

35:16.280 --> 35:17.702
Now, get him
to tell the truth.

35:17.740 --> 35:20.868
That's your problem.

35:20.910 --> 35:23.549
CUESTA:
All right, enough, enough.
The witness...

35:23.580 --> 35:26.185
*

35:47.470 --> 35:50.303
(door closes)
KALIN DA:
Cary.

35:50.340 --> 35:51.739
Look.

35:51.780 --> 35:53.941
I will talk to him again.

35:53.980 --> 35:55.379
No.

35:55.420 --> 35:57.615
You can't.

35:57.650 --> 36:00.244
You can't take the plea.

36:03.890 --> 36:05.949
Four months ago...

36:05.990 --> 36:09.289
my life was... it was just that,
it was my life,

36:09.330 --> 36:12.390
and now I don't know what it is.

36:12.430 --> 36:15.797
I go from one nightmare
to another,

36:15.840 --> 36:18.707
and I just want it to be over.

36:18.740 --> 36:21.379
They're gonna
convict me.

36:21.410 --> 36:23.378
We don't have a case.

36:23.410 --> 36:25.207
I look at the jury...

36:25.250 --> 36:28.242
and they want to put me away.

36:28.280 --> 36:30.510
(door opens)
DIANE:
Cary,

36:30.550 --> 36:33.348
do you have
a minute?
Oh, yeah.

36:36.260 --> 36:38.854
Geneva has a new offer.
(clears throat)

36:38.890 --> 36:40.619
Mr. Agos.

36:42.260 --> 36:43.557
Hello.

36:44.600 --> 36:46.363
The state's attorney

36:46.400 --> 36:48.288
is prepared to offer
time served,

36:48.340 --> 36:50.262
with six months' probation.

36:50.300 --> 36:52.268
Really?

36:52.310 --> 36:54.301
If you testify against Bishop.

36:59.050 --> 37:01.371
(sighs)

37:01.420 --> 37:02.478
(sniffs)

37:02.520 --> 37:04.579
I can't do that.
I understand.

37:04.620 --> 37:06.315
Then we're prepared to offer

37:06.350 --> 37:08.250
a lighter sentence
on the conspiracy charge.

37:08.290 --> 37:09.609
Four years.

37:09.660 --> 37:12.322
DIANE:
With tiane served?
0.

37:12.360 --> 37:16.023
With day-for-day good time,
that's two years in prison.

37:16.060 --> 37:18.369
That's the best you'll ever get.

37:20.370 --> 37:22.361
(departing footsteps)

37:24.370 --> 37:27.009
*

37:27.040 --> 37:29.008
What do you think?

37:29.040 --> 37:31.406
Uh, I think I'm angry.
She's not
wrong, Cary.

37:31.450 --> 37:33.771
We go to jury, you
might get 15 years.

37:33.810 --> 37:36.813
That's seven and a
half in real time.

37:36.850 --> 37:39.387
Or you get out
when you're 37.

37:40.390 --> 37:44.429
It all comes crashing down.

37:44.460 --> 37:47.020
Cary, where are you going?
I need some air.

37:48.060 --> 37:50.255
(Cary sighs)

37:55.500 --> 37:57.036
How's he doing?

37:57.070 --> 37:58.958
DIANE:
I don't know. It's so hard.

37:59.010 --> 38:01.331
I can't imagine
being in his position.

38:01.380 --> 38:03.439
Where is he?

38:03.480 --> 38:05.778
Um, downstairs walking.

38:05.810 --> 38:07.072
I'm coming over.

38:07.110 --> 38:09.874
Yep. I think that would be good.

38:09.920 --> 38:12.081
What do you think he should do?

38:12.120 --> 38:13.883
Take the four years or fight?

38:13.920 --> 38:17.356
Yes.
(heavy sigh)

38:17.390 --> 38:19.927
I have no idea.

38:19.960 --> 38:23.452
Oh, did you really threaten
to knife

38:23.500 --> 38:26.094
your daughter's P.E. teacher?

38:26.130 --> 38:28.496
Not one of my better moments.

38:28.540 --> 38:30.565
I'll see you.

38:30.600 --> 38:32.909
NEWSMAN: ...claiming that
the note Al_icia Florrick wrote
(quietly): Yes.

38:32.940 --> 38:34.635
in which she threatened
to stab a teacher
What? What happened?

38:34.680 --> 38:35.829
...was intended as a joke.

38:35.880 --> 38:36.904
SLAVICK:
Mrs. Florrick is

38:36.940 --> 38:38.441
a perfect parent.

38:38.480 --> 38:40.948
She was joking
with her daughter, that's all.

38:40.980 --> 38:42.379
I want to be clear.

38:42.420 --> 38:45.082
We take school violence
seriously.

38:45.120 --> 38:46.985
But this was purely
a misunderstanding.

38:47.020 --> 38:48.351
Mrs. Florrick

38:48.390 --> 38:50.608
has been a real friend
of our school and...

38:50.660 --> 38:51.684
(click)

38:53.160 --> 38:54.593
You guys didn't...

38:54.630 --> 38:55.790
Didn't what?
Offer patronage.

38:55.830 --> 38:57.388
I said I wouldn't do that.

38:57.430 --> 38:58.567
And you didn't.
You're saying

38:58.600 --> 38:59.828
that_ these teachers
just changed

38:59.870 --> 39:01.098
their mind?
Yeah. After getting seats

39:01.130 --> 39:02.768
on the Illinois
Safety Commission.

39:08.040 --> 39:11.077
Peter.
Yep. He had
some empty seats

39:11.110 --> 39:13.578
on a new commission
he formed.
So that's good--

39:13.610 --> 39:15.373
you didn't offer patronage.

39:15.420 --> 39:16.717
Yep.

39:16.750 --> 39:18.809
*

39:40.470 --> 39:43.633
*

39:46.450 --> 39:48.099
Cary.

39:48.150 --> 39:50.368
How are you?

39:51.790 --> 39:53.712
Hunlq-dory.

39:53.750 --> 39:55.650
Would you like to talk?

39:57.460 --> 39:59.849
Sure. Why not?

40:08.470 --> 40:11.439
You've been good, Cary.

40:11.470 --> 40:14.132
Thank you.

40:14.170 --> 40:16.673
I know what
you're up against.

40:16.710 --> 40:18.439
Four years.

40:18.480 --> 40:20.448
That's a hard one.

40:20.480 --> 40:22.778
Trial's not over yet.

40:22.820 --> 40:24.913
(sighs): Yeah.

40:24.950 --> 40:26.645
It is.

40:26.690 --> 40:29.750
They want you.

40:29.790 --> 40:32.156
They'll get you.

40:32.190 --> 40:34.750
I have a way to move you
out of the country.

40:34.800 --> 40:39.499
You won't be able to return,
but I'll get you an apartment.

40:39.530 --> 40:42.658
I need a legal consultant
in Europe.

40:42.700 --> 40:45.009
It'll be good pay.

40:45.040 --> 40:48.635
I'm not being
purely selfless.

40:48.680 --> 40:52.172
I need someone loyal
that can help me.

40:55.080 --> 40:57.173
Where would it be?

40:57.220 --> 40:59.541
Barcelona.

40:59.590 --> 41:01.581
What do you think?

41:04.560 --> 41:07.882
(sighs): Uh, I think
that I can't do that.

41:09.130 --> 41:11.098
Why?
The firm

41:11.130 --> 41:12.620
put up $1.3 million.

41:12.670 --> 41:14.763
I jump bail,
they don't get that back.

41:14.800 --> 41:17.735
So send them the money
from overseas.

41:17.770 --> 41:21.604
Don't go to jail for four years
because of a law firm.

41:27.180 --> 41:28.818
(bell dings)

41:36.660 --> 41:39.288
So...

41:39.330 --> 41:41.594
how's it going?

41:41.630 --> 41:44.292
Not good,
from the sound of things.

41:44.330 --> 41:45.695
Eh.

41:45.730 --> 41:47.527
Momentary setback.

41:55.680 --> 41:57.830
You got to fight it, Cary.

41:57.880 --> 41:59.245
(sighs): No.

41:59.280 --> 42:01.077
(chuckles):
No, I don't.

42:01.110 --> 42:02.816
Four years.

42:02.850 --> 42:05.614
Two years for good behavior.
And you didn't do it.

42:05.650 --> 42:06.742
I know.

42:06.790 --> 42:08.712
I'll be 37.
I can do that.

42:08.760 --> 42:10.819
I can't do 15 years.

42:10.860 --> 42:13.078
(whispers):
Dear Lord, Cary.
What are you gonna do?

42:13.130 --> 42:15.894
The choices have
been reduced.

42:15.930 --> 42:18.569
We can appeal.
I mean, you take the plea,

42:18.600 --> 42:20.568
you can't appeal.
Alicia...

42:20.600 --> 42:23.694
I have watched you long enough
with clients to know

42:23.740 --> 42:27.164
when you have a case
or when you don't.

42:27.210 --> 42:30.771
The smart deal here
is to take the plea.

42:39.690 --> 42:41.954
You'll come and see me?

42:45.760 --> 42:47.625
(crying):
I will.

42:47.660 --> 42:48.797
Good, good.

42:48.830 --> 42:51.958
I don't want to be lonely.

42:53.170 --> 42:55.161
(crying softly)

42:57.240 --> 43:00.767
CUESTA:
Would you like to revise
your plea, Mr. Agos?

43:06.680 --> 43:08.648
Yes, Your Honor.
I would like to plead guilty.

